{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":806,"text":"Imagine that you invented a device"},{"time":2905,"text":"that can record my memories,"},{"time":4601,"text":"my dreams, my ideas,"},{"time":6662,"text":"and transmit them to your brain."},{"time":8755,"text":"That would be a game-changing\ntechnology, right?"},{"time":11854,"text":"But in fact, we already\npossess this device,"},{"time":14916,"text":"and it's called human communication system"},{"time":17584,"text":"and effective storytelling."},{"time":19874,"text":"To understand how this device works,"},{"time":22358,"text":"we have to look into our brains."},{"time":24797,"text":"And we have to formulate the question\nin a slightly different manner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28407,"text":"Now we have to ask"},{"time":30309,"text":"how these neuron patterns in my brain"},{"time":32949,"text":"that are associated\nwith my memories and ideas"},{"time":36175,"text":"are transmitted into your brains."},{"time":39702,"text":"And we think there are two factors\nthat enable us to communicate."},{"time":43094,"text":"First, your brain is now\nphysically coupled to the sound wave"},{"time":47173,"text":"that I'm transmitting to your brain."},{"time":49672,"text":"And second, we developed\na common neural protocol"},{"time":53074,"text":"that enabled us to communicate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55459,"text":"So how do we know that?"},{"time":57292,"text":"In my lab in Princeton,"},{"time":59209,"text":"we bring people to the fMRI scanner\nand we scan their brains"},{"time":62738,"text":"while they are either telling\nor listening to real-life stories."},{"time":66662,"text":"And to give you a sense\nof the stimulus we are using,"},{"time":69310,"text":"let me play 20 seconds\nfrom a story that we used,"},{"time":73318,"text":"told by a very talented storyteller,"},{"time":75666,"text":"Jim O'Grady."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78244,"text":"(Audio) Jim O'Grady: So I'm banging out\nmy story and I know it's good,"},{"time":81601,"text":"and then I start to make it better --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":83915,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86423,"text":"by adding an element of embellishment."},{"time":89502,"text":"Reporters call this \"making shit up.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":92834,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":95735,"text":"And they recommend\nagainst crossing that line."},{"time":100208,"text":"But I had just seen the line crossed\nbetween a high-powered dean"},{"time":104836,"text":"and assault with a pastry."},{"time":106286,"text":"And I kinda liked it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":107802,"text":"Uri Hasson: OK, so now\nlet's look into your brain"},{"time":110200,"text":"and see what's happening\nwhen you listen to these kinds of stories."},{"time":113452,"text":"And let's start simple -- let's start\nwith one listener and one brain area:"},{"time":117520,"text":"the auditory cortex that processes\nthe sounds that come from the ear."},{"time":121033,"text":"And as you can see,\nin this particular brain area,"},{"time":123501,"text":"the responses are going up and down\nas the story is unfolding."},{"time":127017,"text":"Now we can take these responses"},{"time":128634,"text":"and compare them to the responses\nin other listeners"},{"time":131459,"text":"in the same brain area."},{"time":132958,"text":"And we can ask:"},{"time":134149,"text":"How similar are the responses\nacross all listeners?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":138018,"text":"So here you can see five listeners."},{"time":140983,"text":"And we start to scan their brains\nbefore the story starts,"},{"time":144460,"text":"when they're simply lying in the dark\nand waiting for the story to begin."},{"time":148023,"text":"As you can see,"},{"time":149201,"text":"the brain area is going up and down\nin each one of them,"},{"time":151983,"text":"but the responses are very different,"},{"time":153782,"text":"and not in sync."},{"time":155473,"text":"However, immediately\nas the story is starting,"},{"time":158203,"text":"something amazing is happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160857,"text":"(Audio) JO: So I'm banging out my story\nand I know it's good,"},{"time":163810,"text":"and then I start to make it --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":165362,"text":"UH: Suddenly, you can see\nthat the responses in all of the subjects"},{"time":168683,"text":"lock to the story,"},{"time":169859,"text":"and now they are going up and down\nin a very similar way"},{"time":173312,"text":"across all listeners."},{"time":174890,"text":"And in fact, this is exactly\nwhat is happening now in your brains"},{"time":177963,"text":"when you listen to my sound speaking."},{"time":180860,"text":"We call this effect \"neural entrainment.\""},{"time":184374,"text":"And to explain to you\nwhat is neural entrainment,"},{"time":186710,"text":"let me first explain\nwhat is physical entrainment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190076,"text":"So, we'll look and see five metronomes."},{"time":192850,"text":"Think of these five metronomes\nas five brains."},{"time":195870,"text":"And similar to the listeners\nbefore the story starts,"},{"time":198644,"text":"these metronomes are going to click,"},{"time":200481,"text":"but they're going to click out of phase."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203059,"text":"(Clicking)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":207479,"text":"Now see what will happen\nwhen I connect them together"},{"time":210504,"text":"by placing them on these two cylinders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213880,"text":"(Clicking)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":217125,"text":"Now these two cylinders start to rotate."},{"time":219761,"text":"This rotation vibration\nis going through the wood"},{"time":222914,"text":"and is going to couple\nall the metronomes together."},{"time":225943,"text":"And now listen to the click."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227579,"text":"(Synchronized clicking)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":237834,"text":"This is what you call\nphysical entrainment."},{"time":240482,"text":"Now let's go back to the brain and ask:"},{"time":242749,"text":"What's driving this neural entrainment?"},{"time":244917,"text":"Is it simply the sounds\nthat the speaker is producing?"},{"time":247726,"text":"Or maybe it's the words."},{"time":249073,"text":"Or maybe it's the meaning\nthat the speaker is trying to convey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252743,"text":"So to test it, we did\nthe following experiment."},{"time":255527,"text":"First, we took the story\nand played it backwards."},{"time":258752,"text":"And that preserved many\nof the original auditory features,"},{"time":261902,"text":"but removed the meaning."},{"time":263939,"text":"And it sounds something like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265634,"text":"(Audio) JO: (Unintelligible)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":271296,"text":"And we flashed colors in the two brains"},{"time":273672,"text":"to indicate brain areas that respond\nvery similarly across people."},{"time":277608,"text":"And as you can see,"},{"time":278786,"text":"this incoming sound induced entrainment\nor alignment in all of the brains"},{"time":282578,"text":"in auditory cortices\nthat process the sounds,"},{"time":285334,"text":"but it didn't spread\ndeeper into the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288051,"text":"Now we can take these sounds\nand build words out of it."},{"time":291479,"text":"So if we take Jim O'Grady\nand scramble the words,"},{"time":294159,"text":"we'll get a list of words."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295423,"text":"(Audio) JO: ... an animal ...\nassorted facts ..."},{"time":297709,"text":"and right on ... pie man ...\npotentially ... my stories"}]},{"cues":[{"time":300625,"text":"UH: And you can see that these words\nstart to induce alignment"},{"time":303591,"text":"in early language areas,\nbut not more than that."},{"time":306220,"text":"Now we can take the words\nand start to build sentences out of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311561,"text":"(Audio) JO: And they recommend\nagainst crossing that line."},{"time":316021,"text":"He says: \"Dear Jim,\nGood story. Nice details."},{"time":320369,"text":"Didn't she only know\nabout him through me?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":322545,"text":"UH: Now you can see that the responses\nin all the language areas"},{"time":325704,"text":"that process the incoming language"},{"time":327419,"text":"become aligned or similar\nacross all listeners."},{"time":330218,"text":"However, only when we use\nthe full, engaging, coherent story"},{"time":334919,"text":"do the responses spread\ndeeper into the brain"},{"time":337168,"text":"into higher-order areas,"},{"time":338723,"text":"which include the frontal cortex\nand the parietal cortex,"},{"time":341848,"text":"and make all of them\nrespond very similarly."},{"time":344460,"text":"And we believe that these responses\nin higher-order areas are induced"},{"time":347753,"text":"or become similar across listeners"},{"time":349903,"text":"because of the meaning\nconveyed by the speaker,"},{"time":352667,"text":"and not by words or sound."},{"time":354635,"text":"And if we are right,\nthere's a strong prediction over here"},{"time":357374,"text":"if I tell you the exact same ideas"},{"time":359760,"text":"using two very different sets of words,"},{"time":362428,"text":"your brain responses\nwill still be similar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365499,"text":"And to test it, we did\nthe following experiment in my lab."},{"time":369142,"text":"We took the English story"},{"time":370974,"text":"and translated it to Russian."},{"time":373134,"text":"Now you have two different sounds\nand linguistic systems"},{"time":377382,"text":"that convey the exact same meaning."},{"time":379700,"text":"And you play the English story\nto the English listeners"},{"time":383372,"text":"and the Russian story\nto the Russian listeners,"},{"time":385748,"text":"and we can compare their responses\nacross the groups."},{"time":388817,"text":"And when we did that, we didn't see\nresponses that are similar"},{"time":392412,"text":"in auditory cortices in language,"},{"time":394717,"text":"because the language\nand sound are very different."},{"time":397119,"text":"However, you can see\nthat the responses in high-order areas"},{"time":399921,"text":"were still similar\nacross these two groups."},{"time":403068,"text":"We believe this is because they understood\nthe story in a very similar way,"},{"time":407184,"text":"as we confirmed, using a test\nafter the story ended."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412321,"text":"And we think that this alignment\nis necessary for communication."},{"time":416032,"text":"For example, as you can tell,"},{"time":418682,"text":"I am not a native English speaker."},{"time":420733,"text":"I grew up with another language,"},{"time":422638,"text":"and the same might be for many\nof you in the audience."},{"time":425316,"text":"And still, we can communicate."},{"time":427339,"text":"How come?"},{"time":428514,"text":"We think we can communicate\nbecause we have this common code"},{"time":431617,"text":"that presents meaning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433921,"text":"So far, I've only talked about\nwhat's happening in the listener's brain,"},{"time":437391,"text":"in your brain, when\nyou're listening to talks."},{"time":439662,"text":"But what's happening\nin the speaker's brain, in my brain,"},{"time":442385,"text":"when I'm speaking to you?"},{"time":444216,"text":"To look in the speaker's brain,"},{"time":446097,"text":"we asked the speaker\nto go into the scanner,"},{"time":449217,"text":"we scan his brain"},{"time":450843,"text":"and then compare his brain responses\nto the brain responses of the listeners"},{"time":454874,"text":"listening to the story."},{"time":456700,"text":"You have to remember that producing speech\nand comprehending speech"},{"time":460934,"text":"are very different processes."},{"time":462681,"text":"Here we're asking: How similar are they?"},{"time":466164,"text":"To our surprise,"},{"time":467595,"text":"we saw that all these complex\npatterns within the listeners"},{"time":472490,"text":"actually came from the speaker brain."},{"time":475221,"text":"So production and comprehension\nrely on very similar processes."},{"time":478930,"text":"And we also found"},{"time":480526,"text":"the stronger the similarity\nbetween the listener's brain"},{"time":484256,"text":"and the speaker's brain,"},{"time":485779,"text":"the better the communication."},{"time":487708,"text":"So I know that if you\nare completely confused now,"},{"time":491697,"text":"and I do hope that this is not the case,"},{"time":493742,"text":"your brain responses\nare very different than mine."},{"time":496159,"text":"But I also know that if you really\nunderstand me now,"},{"time":499290,"text":"then your brain ... and your brain\n... and your brain"},{"time":502205,"text":"are really similar to mine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505793,"text":"Now, let's take all\nthis information together and ask:"},{"time":508912,"text":"How can we use it to transmit\na memory that I have"},{"time":512273,"text":"from my brain to your brains?"},{"time":515037,"text":"So we did the following experiment."},{"time":517648,"text":"We let people watch,\nfor the first time in their life,"},{"time":520245,"text":"a TV episode from the BBC series\n\"Sherlock,\" while we scanned their brains."},{"time":524403,"text":"And then we asked them\nto go back to the scanner"},{"time":527228,"text":"and tell the story to another person\nthat never watched the movie."},{"time":531151,"text":"So let's be specific."},{"time":532835,"text":"Think about this exact scene,"},{"time":534906,"text":"when Sherlock is entering\nthe cab in London"},{"time":537514,"text":"driven by the murderer he is looking for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540398,"text":"With me, as a viewer,"},{"time":542918,"text":"there is a specific brain pattern\nin my brain when I watch it."},{"time":547179,"text":"Now, the exact same pattern,\nI can reactivate in my brain again"},{"time":550975,"text":"by telling the word:\nSherlock, London, murderer."},{"time":555369,"text":"And when I'm transmitting\nthese words to your brains now,"},{"time":558503,"text":"you have to reconstruct it in your mind."},{"time":561012,"text":"In fact, we see that pattern\nemerging now in your brains."},{"time":565585,"text":"And we were really surprised to see"},{"time":568124,"text":"that the pattern you have\nnow in your brains"},{"time":570403,"text":"when I'm describing to you these scenes"},{"time":572339,"text":"would be very similar to the pattern\nI had when I watched this movie"},{"time":576185,"text":"a few months ago in the scanner."},{"time":578347,"text":"This starts to tell you\nabout the mechanism"},{"time":580475,"text":"by which we can tell stories\nand transmit information."},{"time":583733,"text":"Because, for example,"},{"time":585633,"text":"now you're listening really hard\nand trying to understand what I'm saying."},{"time":589169,"text":"And I know that it's not easy."},{"time":590743,"text":"But I hope that at one point\nin the talk we clicked, and you got me."},{"time":594803,"text":"And I think that in a few hours,\na few days, a few months,"},{"time":598725,"text":"you're going to meet someone at a party,"},{"time":600893,"text":"and you're going to tell him\nabout this lecture,"},{"time":604465,"text":"and suddenly it will be as if\nhe is standing now here with us."},{"time":608127,"text":"Now you can see\nhow we can take this mechanism"},{"time":611001,"text":"and try to transmit memories\nand knowledge across people,"},{"time":614956,"text":"which is wonderful, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":617027,"text":"But our ability to communicate\nrelies on our ability"},{"time":620218,"text":"to have common ground."},{"time":622808,"text":"Because, for example,"},{"time":624037,"text":"if I'm going to use the British synonym"},{"time":627828,"text":"\"hackney carriage\" instead of \"cab,\""},{"time":630230,"text":"I know that I'm going to be misaligned\nwith most of you in the audience."},{"time":634720,"text":"This alignment depends\nnot only on our ability"},{"time":636935,"text":"to understand the basic concept;"},{"time":638993,"text":"it also depends on our ability to develop\ncommon ground and understanding"},{"time":643812,"text":"and shared belief systems."},{"time":645623,"text":"Because we know that in many cases,"},{"time":647481,"text":"people understand the exact\nsame story in very different ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652460,"text":"So to test it in the lab,\nwe did the following experiment."},{"time":656089,"text":"We took a story by J.D. Salinger,"},{"time":659044,"text":"in which a husband lost track\nof his wife in the middle of a party,"},{"time":663403,"text":"and he's calling his best friend, asking,\n\"Did you see my wife?\""},{"time":667836,"text":"For half of the subjects,"},{"time":669067,"text":"we said that the wife was having\nan affair with the best friend."},{"time":673232,"text":"For the other half,"},{"time":674407,"text":"we said that the wife is loyal\nand the husband is very jealous."},{"time":680127,"text":"This one sentence before the story started"},{"time":682839,"text":"was enough to make the brain responses"},{"time":685164,"text":"of all the people that believed\nthe wife was having an affair"},{"time":688232,"text":"be very similar in these high-order areas"},{"time":690693,"text":"and different than the other group."},{"time":692939,"text":"And if one sentence is enough\nto make your brain similar"},{"time":696636,"text":"to people that think like you"},{"time":698263,"text":"and very different than people\nthat think differently than you,"},{"time":701240,"text":"think how this effect is going\nto be amplified in real life,"},{"time":704741,"text":"when we are all listening\nto the exact same news item"},{"time":707657,"text":"after being exposed\nday after day after day"},{"time":711429,"text":"to different media channels,\nlike Fox News or The New York Times,"},{"time":715265,"text":"that give us very different\nperspectives on reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719556,"text":"So let me summarize."},{"time":721529,"text":"If everything worked as planned tonight,"},{"time":723642,"text":"I used my ability to vocalize sound\nto be coupled to your brains."},{"time":727965,"text":"And I used this coupling"},{"time":729492,"text":"to transmit my brain patterns associated\nwith my memories and ideas"},{"time":733357,"text":"into your brains."},{"time":735201,"text":"In this, I start to reveal\nthe hidden neural mechanism"},{"time":739023,"text":"by which we communicate."},{"time":740682,"text":"And we know that in the future\nit will enable us to improve"},{"time":743673,"text":"and facilitate communication."},{"time":746111,"text":"But these studies also reveal"},{"time":748535,"text":"that communication relies\non a common ground."},{"time":751845,"text":"And we have to be\nreally worried as a society"},{"time":754331,"text":"if we lose this common ground\nand our ability to speak with people"},{"time":758391,"text":"that are slightly different than us"},{"time":760532,"text":"because we let a few very strong\nmedia channels"},{"time":763944,"text":"take control of the mic,"},{"time":765509,"text":"and manipulate and control\nthe way we all think."},{"time":769308,"text":"And I'm not sure how to fix it\nbecause I'm only a scientist."},{"time":772233,"text":"But maybe one way to do it"},{"time":774717,"text":"is to go back to the more\nnatural way of communication,"},{"time":777388,"text":"which is a dialogue,"},{"time":779014,"text":"in which it's not only me\nspeaking to you now,"},{"time":781994,"text":"but a more natural way of talking,"},{"time":784234,"text":"in which I am speaking and I am listening,"},{"time":787535,"text":"and together we are trying to come\nto a common ground and new ideas."},{"time":792279,"text":"Because after all,"},{"time":793461,"text":"the people we are coupled to\ndefine who we are."},{"time":797149,"text":"And our desire to be coupled\nto another brain"},{"time":799562,"text":"is something very basic\nthat starts at a very early age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804103,"text":"So let me finish with an example\nfrom my own private life"},{"time":809044,"text":"that I think is a good example\nof how coupling to other people"},{"time":813379,"text":"is really going to define who we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816294,"text":"This my son Jonathan at a very early age."},{"time":819392,"text":"See how he developed\na vocal game together with my wife,"},{"time":823566,"text":"only from the desire and pure joy\nof being coupled to another human being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829556,"text":"(Both vocalizing)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":842915,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":845267,"text":"Now, think how the ability of my son"},{"time":849088,"text":"to be coupled to us\nand other people in his life"},{"time":851874,"text":"is going to shape the man\nhe is going to become."},{"time":854756,"text":"And think how you change on a daily basis"},{"time":857195,"text":"from the interaction and coupling\nto other people in your life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":862562,"text":"So keep being coupled to other people."},{"time":865157,"text":"Keep spreading your ideas,"},{"time":866730,"text":"because the sum of all of us\ntogether, coupled,"},{"time":869998,"text":"is greater than our parts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871616,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872806,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}